The enhanced ZT values in these nanostructured and/or complex-structured materials are attributed to reduced lattice thermal conductivity caused by phonon boundary and defect scattering by nanostructures. This idea is best illustrated by a very recent report by Kanatzidis and co-workers15 in which ZT beyond 2 is achieved in PbTe. The high ZT is due to extremely low κL\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
