				\begin{document}$$ \kappa_{\text{L}} $$\end{document} are ~2.5 and ~1.2 W/m K at 800 K for Mg2Si, Ref. 35 and Mg2(SiSn), Ref. 12, respectively), presuming due to the stronger alloy scattering in Mg2(SiSn) alloys.Fig. 4
Mechanochemical synthesis and thermoelectric properties of Mg2Si. (a) An SEM image shows Mg2Si particles ranging in size from nanometers to microns. (b) A TEM image shows that Mg2Si aggregates are made up of smaller particles and crystallites. (c) ZT of samples with various Bi doping concentrations from 300 K to 800 K. For samples with near-optimum carrier concentrations, ZT values of 0.7 are obtained at 775 K (Reprinted with permission from Ref. [35], Copyright 2011, Royal Society of Chemistry)
